FBIS3-45961 "drchi016_m_94009" FBIS-CHI-94-016 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Jan 1994 Military More Military Airports Renovated For Civilian Use OW2001074794 Beijing XINHUA in English 0730 GMT 20 Jan 94 OW2001074794 Beijing XINHUA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Beijing, January 20 (XINHUA) -- Increasing numbers of military airports are being expanded or renovated for civil use in China to meet the needs of the national economic advance. In the past ten years a total of 31 military airports have been expanded and renovated with funds jointly supplied by local governments and the military, and are usually jointly managed. Last year alone 11 military airports completed their expansion work. The opening of Gonggar airport, a military airport in Lhasa, capital of the Tibet Autonomous Region, to civilian use has helped the city to operate a dozen domestic air routes to Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou, Chengdu and other major cities.
